340 g Turkey Breast Portions
¾ cup Basmati Rice
113 g Snow Peas
1 unit(s) Sweet Bell Pepper
2 unit(s) Green Onion
2 unit(s) Honey
1 tbsp Soy Sauce
4 g Garlic Salt
2 unit(s) Garlic, cloves
1 tbsp Seasoned Rice Vinegar
1 tbsp Sesame Oil
9 g Sesame Seeds
2 tbsp Butter*
2 tbsp Oil*
0.06 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Before starting, wash and dry all produce.
Peel, then mince or grate garlic.
To a medium pot, add 1 1/4 cups (2 1/2 cups) water, 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) butter, garlic and half the garlic salt. Cover and bring to a boil over high.
Using a strainer, rinse rice until water runs clear.
To the boiling water, add rice, then reduce heat to low. Cover and cook for 13-15 min, until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.
Remove from heat. Set aside, still covered.

Meanwhile, thinly slice green onion, keeping white and green parts separate.
Trim, then halve snow peas.
Core, then cut pepper into 1/2-inch pieces.
Pat turkey dry with paper towels. On another cutting board, cut into 1-inch pieces. Season with remaining garlic salt and pepper.

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium.
When hot, add sesame seeds to the dry pan. Toast for 2-3 min, stirring often, until golden. (TIP: Keep your eye on them so they don't burn!)
Transfer to a plate.

Reheat the same pan (from step 3) over medium-high.
When hot, add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil, then peppers and snow peas. Cook for 3-4 min, stirring occasionally, until tender.
Add green onion whites. Season with salt and pepper. Cook for 1 min, stirring often, until fragrant.
Transfer veggies to a plate and cover to keep warm.
Carefully wipe the pan clean.

Reheat the same pan over medium.
When hot, add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil, then turkey. Cook for 3-4 min per side, until golden and cooked through.**
Remove pan from heat.
Add half the soy sauce (use all for 4 servings), sesame oil, 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) butter, seasoned vinegar and honey. Cook for 1 min, stirring often, until glazed and coated.

Divide rice, turkey and veggies between plates.
Drizzle remaining glaze over turkey.
Sprinkle remaining green onions over rice.
Sprinkle sesame seeds over turkey and veggies.